---
description: Enforce the specification, approval, implementation and independent verification workflow for new tasks.
alwaysApply: true
---

- New non-bugfix work uses stable IDs in the form `TASK-001`, `TASK-002`, and so on.
- A new task must have a specification under `docs/agent-tasks/` before implementation planning begins.
- Production code must not be changed until both the task specification and implementation plan are human-approved.
- Work on exactly one task ID at a time.
- Bugfixes from `docs/agent-backlog/` continue to use the separate P0/P1/P2 bugfix workflow.
- The approved task specification is the source of truth for expected behavior.
- The approved implementation plan is the source of truth for implementation scope.
- An implementer must not approve its own specification, plan, or implementation.
- Verification must inspect the actual diff and execute relevant commands.
- Do not silently add requirements, remove acceptance criteria, or expand scope.
- When requirements are ambiguous, document assumptions and open decisions instead of inventing behavior.
